'''Charlie Brown''' was a monk located in [[Hosidius]], up the ladder in the small church to the south (which has since been replaced with monk camping site). When spoken to, he revealed that he had journeyed to Great Kourend in search of luck and fortune,{{CiteNPC|npc=Charlie Brown|quote=I've come to Kourend in search of luck, [player name]. I seek many fortunes and as you know you need luck to find fortune!}} and wears [[monk's robes]] to keep him holy when praying to [[Arengeesus]], the Goddess of Luck.{{CiteNPC|npc=Charlie Brown|quote=Ah these robes keeps me holy, I must remain holy when praying to the God of Luck}}{{CiteNPC|npc=Charlie Brown|quote=Arengeesus, God of luck. We do not know much about her or where she comes from, we just know she is there looking over us.}}

He claimed those who praise Arengeesus enough to get her attention were rewarded with luck on the adventures of those who praised her.{{CiteNPC|npc=Charlie Brown|quote=Those who praise Arengeesus enough to get her attention are rewarded. She will gaze down upon you providing you with luck on your adventures.}} The player then attempted to refute the statement by claiming hard work is all that's needed, but Charlie Brown believed that working hard is a form of praise to Arengeesus.{{CiteNPC|npc=Charlie Brown|quote=[Hard work is all you need.] Perhaps working hard is merely a form of praise to the God of luck, [player name].}}

Following the rework of Hosidius on 23 May 2019, he was removed from the game due to his dialogue being deemed inappropriate.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod West|url=https://twitter.com/JagexWest/status/1132258689644150784|date=25 May 2019|archiveurl=https://archive.is/5Ie5g|archivedate=25 May 2020|quote=Yes. He was initially moved out of the way because of the cringe memes but we felt it best that he just goes completely.}}

